  <front>
    <title>OSPF Two-part Metric</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-ietf-ospf-two-part-metric-00"/>
    <author initials="L." surname="Wang" fullname="Lili Wang"/>
    <author initials="A." surname="Lindem" fullname="Acee Lindem"/>
    <author initials="D." surname="DuBois" fullname="Dave DuBois"/>
    <author initials="V." surname="Julka" fullname="Vibhor Julka"/>
    <author initials="T." surname="McMillan" fullname="Tom McMillan"/>
    <date day="20" month="January" year="2015"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>This document specifies an optional extension to the OSPF protocol,
   to represent the metric on a multi-access network as two parts: the
   metric from a router to the network, and the metric from the network
   to the router.  The router to router metric would be the sum of the
   two.</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
